			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">re: the flag mentioned in comment #1.

There is desire to not have extra flags for the verifier.

This can be done three ways:

(a) disable tests
(b) just use the existing "--pnacl-disable-abi-check"
(c) gain enough confidence to start accepting stuff in list (3) -- possibly we
could duplicate the test coverage via some llvm lit tests that show, for each
architecture, what architectural support we have, or what compiler_rt support we
have.


For now, for convenience / incremental progress, I've left the flag, but it won't be used by any of the tests.

*Remember to remove the flag*!
